page.title: 01 General Review
page.content: This area of land on the southern slopes of Dartmoor is comprised of moorland, heath and farmland.Most of the area is within the{Dartmoor {National Park}and ranges from 150m to 365m in height. The highest point is Butterdon hill.It gives spectacular views, across South Devon, to the coast.A number of paths lead over the moor and legends surround the area. About 33% of the area is taken up by farming . The other two thirds is taken up by rough grazing and moorland which is used for leisure activities such as walking ,camping and{Letter {Boxing}.There are two villages in the south east corner,{Bittaford}and{ {Wrangaton}.
